Pain sucks. Especially when it won't go away and you've gotten massage, adjustments, acupuncture and for me, even expensive stem cell shots.
.
.
.
A few months back, my MUA @malihajkhan told me to check out @barefootrehab - I thought, "No, not another pain doctor."
Long story short, I've gotten treated 4 times and I have more relief than anything I've tried, even stem cell treatments. 😭😱💰
.
.
.
And I plan on going back. If you're in the NYC area and you've had chronic pain over 6 months and want relief, check out @barefootrehab in Denville, NJ. It's about 60 mins from the city.
.
.
.
.
.
Also i want to add your diet , movement and hydration is super important. And your mental health ! Lord i can not stress how important that is!

Was so much fun shooting with you @nargisfakhri ❤️

Feeling incredibly blessed and grateful to have worked with such an amazingly talented and passionate team. What an unforgettable experience it was!

A huge shoutout to @yoyohoneysingh , @mihirgulati , @grini_f and each and every member of the crew — your creativity, energy, and dedication were truly inspiring. The passion in the air was palpable, and being surrounded by such brilliance made every moment feel electric.

Our two days at Tijara Fort palace felt like stepping into an ancient tale — a world of magic, music, and raw emotion. It was nothing short of surreal.

Thank you all for making this journey so special. I carry the memories with a full heart and immense gratitude.

God has truly been kind to me.

Thank you @mahakbrahmawar

latestPosts.caption:
Old-Hollywood grace collides with modern aesthetics as Nargis Fakhri (@nargisfakhri) steps into her most stylish era-where fashion becomes both armour and art. The actor is the epitome of sensuality as she strikes a pose with her big hair and berry red lipstick. A dramatic interplay of sensuality and sophistication, this ensemble from Roseroom by Isha J (@roseroom__official) features a sculpted black bodysuit adorned with delicate lace placements that trace the contours of the body with quiet allure. Paired with a sweeping floor-length jacket, the look transforms into a vision of regal mystery. The jacket’s exaggerated bell sleeves are brought to life with opulent couture hand embroidery—an ode to french architectural motifs and dainty laces, glimmering with antique metallic threads, swarovski, and crystals. Her look has been spruced up with a striking pendant from Diacolor @dia_logues. 

Roseroom By Isha J (@roseroom__official) will be partaking in FDCI (@fdciofficial) Manifest Wedding Weekend on 2-3 August 2025, at Taj Palace, New Delhi.
